---
// ComparisonPlate.astro - Side-by-side contrast of Compliance vs. Physics governance
---

<div class="comparison-plate-container">
  <div class="comparison-header">Governance Paradigms Compared</div>
  
  <div class="comparison-grid">
    <!-- Paradigm A: Compliance -->
    <div class="comparison-column column-compliance">
      <div class="column-title">Compliance-Layer Governance</div>
      <div class="column-subtitle">Post-Hoc Verification (SynthID Model)</div>
      
      <div class="comparison-item">
        <div class="item-label">Operational Focus</div>
        <div class="item-value">Output monitoring and post-hoc metadata watermarking. Analyzes generated content at the edge of the pipeline.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="comparison-item">
        <div class="item-label">Structural Boundary</div>
        <div class="item-value">Soft policies. Rules are stated in textual allowlists, prompts, or license agreements.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="comparison-item">
        <div class="item-label">Vulnerability Profile</div>
        <div class="item-value font-mono-text">Surgically defeatable. Carrier watermarks are easily stripped or forged using 2D Fourier phase coherence analysis.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Paradigm B: Physics -->
    <div class="comparison-column column-physics">
      <div class="column-title">Physics-Layer Governance</div>
      <div class="column-subtitle">Structural Constraint (FunctionGemma + MCP + Torus)</div>
      
      <div class="comparison-item">
        <div class="item-label font-sovereign-text">Operational Focus</div>
        <div class="item-value">Local execution containment, schema contract verification, and network routing limitations.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="comparison-item">
        <div class="item-label font-sovereign-text">Structural Boundary</div>
        <div class="item-value">Hard limits. Constraints are compiled into edge model weights and hardware routing paths.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="comparison-item">
        <div class="item-label font-sovereign-text">Vulnerability Profile</div>
        <div class="item-value font-mono-text">Topology-locked. Rogue actions are starved of bandwidth by hardware interconnect feedback loops.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .comparison-plate-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin: var(--space-8) auto;
    padding: var(--space-6);
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    max-width: var(--max-w-wide);
  }
  .comparison-header {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: bold;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .comparison-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }
  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .comparison-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }
  .comparison-column {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    padding: var(--space-5);
    background: var(--surface-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-mid);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  }
  .column-compliance {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--border-dim);
  }
  .column-physics {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-sovereign);
    background: rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.01);
  }
  .column-title {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: bold;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .column-subtitle {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    margin-top: -10px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .comparison-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-1);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
    padding-top: var(--space-3);
  }
  .item-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .font-sovereign-text {
    color: var(--color-sovereign);
    font-weight: bold;
  }
  .item-value {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
  }
  .font-mono-text {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }
</style>
